Module Name:
Web Application

Objective:
To develop a user-friendly web application that provides crop recommendations based on soil nutrients and environmental conditions.

Introduction:
The Web Application module serves as the interface between the user and the crop recommendation system. It allows users to enter agricultural parameters and receive suitable crop recommendations instantly.

Technology Stack:
• Python
• Flask
• HTML
• CSS

Files Used:
1. app.py
2. templates/index.html
3. static/style.css
4. requirements.txt

Input Parameters:
• Nitrogen (N)
• Phosphorus (P)
• Potassium (K)
• Temperature
• Humidity
• pH Value
• Rainfall

Working Procedure:

Step 1:
The user enters soil and environmental parameters through the web form.

Step 2:
The Flask application receives the input values.

Step 3:
The system processes the input data.

Step 4:
Crop recommendation logic is executed.

Step 5:
The recommended crop is displayed on the web page.

Features:
• User-friendly interface
• Easy data entry
• Fast crop recommendation
• Responsive web application

Advantages:
• Supports smart agriculture
• Reduces decision-making time
• Improves farming efficiency
• Simple and easy to use

Output:
Recommended Crop

Expected Result:
The application successfully recommends a suitable crop based on the provided soil and environmental conditions.

Conclusion:
The Web Application module provides an effective interface for interacting with the OptiCrop system. It enables users to obtain crop recommendations quickly and efficiently through a web-based platform.
